<subSubSection id="C368652E93528E0FF2AAFB89FD26FB92" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593528E0FF2AAFB89FD26FB92" blockId="11.[151,1436,1051,1329]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893528E0FF2AAFB89FD22FB92" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147328" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF02BFB89FDACFBFE" box="[534,637,1051,1077]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a female bearing labels “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF181FB89FBDAFBFE" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[956,1035,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF181FB89FBDAFBFE" box="[956,1035,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">luridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Hispania” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF734FB89FAADFBFE" box="[1289,1404,1051,1077]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF2AAFBADFDD1FB92" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[151,512,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF2AAFBADFEB2FB92" box="[151,355,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Acupalpus luridus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493528E0FF356FBADFDD1FB92" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[363,512,1087,1113]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="2687537393528E0FF04EFBADFD38FB92" box="[627,745,1087,1113]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93528E0FF2FAFBF1FAB7FAFA" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593528E0FF2FAFBF1FA45FAC6" blockId="11.[151,1436,1051,1329]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">
The name is currently considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF0D6FBF1FBAFFBB6" authority="(Sturm, 1825)" baseAuthorityName="Sturm" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[747,1150,1122,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF0D6FBF1FC06FBB6" box="[747,983,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Acupalpus flavicollis</emphasis>
(Sturm, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
(see Jaeger, 1989). As in the case of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF328FB15FE31FB6B" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[277,480,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF328FB15FE31FB6B" box="[277,480,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Acupalpus atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF098FB15FCC2FB6A" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[677,787,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF098FB15FCC2FB6A" box="[677,787,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">A. luridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Dejean had been already validly published by Sturm in 1825. It is strange that Dejean did not notice Sturm’s work, as Dejean himself mentioned that he worked with the 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793528E0FF2AAFB5DFF16FB22" box="[151,199,1231,1257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">type</typeStatus>
material sent by Sturm. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493528E0FF3E5FB5DFDA0FB22" author="Jaeger, B." box="[472,625,1231,1257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" pagination="237 - 248" refId="ref10894" refString="Jaeger, B. (1988) Systematik und Verbreitung von Acupalpus dubius Schilsky, 1888 sowie Bemerkungen zur Synonymie und Verbreitung von A. oliveirae Reitter, 1884 und A. notatus Muls. et Rey, 1861 (Col., Carabidae). Entomologische Nachrichten und Berichte, 32 (6), 237 - 248." type="journal article" year="1988">Jaeger (1988)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the nomenclatural problems involving 
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF6A4FB5DFA4DFB22" box="[1177,1436,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF6A4FB5DFAD4FB22" authorityName="Schilsky" authorityYear="1888" box="[1177,1285,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">A. dubius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF732FB5DFA4DFB22" baseAuthorityName="Sturm" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[1295,1436,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">A. flavicollis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and other taxa of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF366FB61FE00FAC6" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1829" box="[347,465,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF366FB61FE00FAC6" box="[347,465,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Acupalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, either with or without a dorsal pore in the second half of the third interval of elytron.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593528E0FF2FAFA85FAB7FAFA" blockId="11.[151,1436,1051,1329]" box="[199,1382,1302,1329]" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693528E0FF2FAFA85FD95FAFA" authority="Sturm, 1825" authorityName="Sturm" authorityYear="1825" box="[199,580,1302,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicollis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793528E0FF2FAFA85FE63FAFA" box="[199,434,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Acupalpus flavicollis</emphasis>
Sturm, 1825
</taxonomicName>
is found in Europe, to the east it reaches 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593528E0FF62EFA85FB47FAFA" box="[1043,1174,1303,1329]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593528E0FF6F6FA85FAB7FAFA" box="[1227,1382,1303,1329]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="11" pageNumber="495">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
